''Look at that baby,'' Bucky Dent said. ''Awesome, isn't it?''

He was dwarfed by 9,000 cement blocks, reinforced by three tons of steel and a quarter mile's worth of pilings sunk into the sandy Florida soil.

The wall is painted a color that might be described as Fenway green.

This structure is neither a wind screen nor a training center for itinerant jai-alai players. It is a replica of the most famous wall in North America.

Soon it will be painted - a string of six zeroes for the team from New York, punctuated by a glaring ''3'' in the seventh inning.

This cement-block wall will look almost exactly like the wall in Boston on the afternoon of Oct. 2, 1978. One concession will be a painted ladder instead of a real metal ladder.